addboard & deleteboard:
 -d domaintag -> from the Domain Tag column
 SB## -> the system board that is being added or deleted from this domain
f15ksc0:sms-svc:2> deleteboard -d gdvp4rdmapp1 SB10 -> deletes the SB10 system board from domain gdvp4rdmapp1
f15ksc0:sms-svc:2> addboard -d gdvp4rdmapp1 SB10 -> adds the SB10 system board to the gdvp4rdmapp1 domain
f15ksc0:sms-svc:2> addboard -d gdvp4rdmapp1 -c configure SB10 -> add the "-c configure" if this is a new board for this domain
**NOTE**
   -these commands can take several minutes

assign SB10
assign SB10 done
poweron SB10
.....
poweron SB10 done
test SB10
........                      
test SB10 done
connect SB10
........
connect SB10 done
configure SB10
..
configure SB10 done
..
notify online SUNW_cpu/cpu320
notify online SUNW_cpu/cpu321
notify online SUNW_cpu/cpu322
notify online SUNW_cpu/cpu323
............                  
notify add capacity (4 cpus)
notify add capacity (1048576 pages)
notify add capacity SB10 done


from domain:
prtdiag -v - check for SB## that was added or removed to confirm